Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugzhk2-O0Y3uiUGIg8h4AaABAg,,@thomastimlin1724,"Yvonne was played by French refugee  actress Madeline Lebeau, who was only 18/19 years old when they filmed this in1942. Her husband is actor Marcel Dalio, who played Emil the croupier [roulette wheel operator and general manager of the  gambling. room.. In June 1940, Lebeau and Dalio (who was Jewish) fled Paris ahead of the invading German Army and reached Lisbon. Sounds familiar doesn't it? They divorced shortly after the  film was made. Lebeau has the  honor of being the last surviving cast member of  Casablanca. Born on 10 June 1923, died 1 May 2016 (aged 92).",2026-05-02T21:02:23Z,2026-05-02T21:02:23Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:00:56.807401
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwIFU-4Bpvhw6nWQlV4AaABAg,,@BenjWarrant,"""Play it, Sam. You played it for her - if she can stand it, I can stand it!"" ""Of all the gin joints in all the towns in the world, she walks into mine."" ""Here's looking at you, kid!"" ""Round up the usual suspects!"" ""I'm shocked, shocked do you hear, to learn that gambling is going on in this establishment."" ""Louis, I think this is the beginning of a beautiful friendship."" ""How extravagant you are with women, Rick."" ""I remember. The Germans wore grey, you wore blue.""",2026-05-02T20:35:29Z,2026-05-02T20:35:29Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:00:56.807404
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwgIcZRP7UhXtbUW414AaABAg,,@jimgreen2080,"Glad you have already said you'll want to see this again. You'll pick up details you missed, and despite knowing what happens will be fully engaged again. The direction, the cinematography--as a wartime production they may not have had a broad landscape canvas to use, but employing light, shadow, super closeups, etc. was brilliant, and the acting is first-rate. BTW, a number of the actors fled the Nazi regime IRL, including Peter ""Ugarte"" Lorre {Jewish) and Conrad Veidt, who played Major Strasser---his wife was Jewish.",2026-05-02T20:31:39Z,2026-05-02T20:31:39Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:00:56.807407
