Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugw4IxZ3Hh5DK16f7Ox4AaABAg,,@kinokind293,"There are precious few movies that on might consider to be ""perfect,"" But this is certainly one (""12 Angry Men"" is another, and ""Sunset Boulevard""). The script is brilliant, as is the acting (direction, cinematography, score . . .). The actors were almost all refugees from the Nazis (even the ones playing Nazis!), which is why there is so much real emotion evident. But among all its perfection, it is ironic that it was still being written during filming! Bogart and Bergman didn't know who Ilsa was going to end up with until nearly the end! This film is one that warrants limitless repeat viewing. I've seen it many times, and it never gets old. There are at least 6 languages being spoken by characters in Rick's, and those reactors conversant in them have translated their dialog as all being appropriate to their situations. Who would do that today!",2026-05-02T05:08:59Z,2026-05-02T05:18:22Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:00:56.807550
