Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugx8xMLcE4kItRryfo14AaABAg.AWHxu9eQRXwAWJ6sv_PzXy,Ugx8xMLcE4kItRryfo14AaABAg,@buretto66,"Rick and the US were not analogs, though.  Rick was a distressed idealist, evidenced by Louie and Victor citing his anti-fascist history for Spain and Ethiopia.  Fights the US never wanted wanted any part of, even if they had been politically aligned, which they weren't.  People should understand, the Allies (aside from the Soviets..who had their own authoritarian issues) were not intrinsically anti-fascist. It's just that, once dragged into war, the enemy nations were fascist.  To quote the late, great George Carlin, in referencing the last time Americans bombed white people... ""They wanted to dominate the world!  Bullsh*t.  That's OUR f*cking job!""",2026-05-02T13:17:26Z,2026-05-02T13:18:10Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:00:57.953631
