Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgzOhtUUcEoexY0b4Gp4AaABAg,,@kishlight1,"I live and work in Dublin city and without any doubt every Dubliner will tell tourists at stay away from the Temple Bar area, it's certainly not only the Temple Bar pub, it's a whole area stretching from Fleet Street in the east to Parliament Street in the west and from Dame Street to the river. It's about as cultural as a set of traffic lights. The overcrowding and over pricing is only the start of its unpleasantness though; streets being used as toilets then because of the Irish governments acceptance of homelessness as normal the whole temple bar area is crowded with the homeless and their begging cups looking for "" spare change"" or a cigarette coupled with this open drug dealing is commonplace, I mean all drugs  from weed, to coke to crack and everything in between.  A particular area on the east end of Temple Bar at the river called Aston Quay is, without exaggerating sometimes like a scene from Mad Max with competing drugs gangs and users regularly engaging in street warfare, it's truly dystopian. In summary The Temple Bar area could legitimately be described as the epitome of tourist scalping and an indictment of Irish government social policy wrapped up in sleek Plastic Paddy PR.   *** STAY AWAY FROM TEMPLE BAR ***",2026-05-02T14:07:13Z,2026-05-02T14:09:12Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:02:03.999242
Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgwpnVXktZx7Hl5vdEB4AaABAg,,@MariaC-yg6uw,"😄no (organised) experience?? 
Oh dear, how did centuries of travelers managed to be entertained 😉
Just back from Pisa, it's beautiful, absolutely packed with tourists, but well worth a visit, lots of history. It's not suffocating + there are 3 other places to visit in the area (bulk tickets) + 2 museums, we spent the whole day there.
Been to Taj Mahal, Marrakesh (people were lovely, felt very safe as a woman and it's beautiful - and the souk is not designed to 'trick you', it's how it was for decades....), Checkpoint Charlie, Blue Lagoon, Venice - you make your own experience of those, even with all the tourist traps. 
Not everything has to be instagram worthy.
But got money stolen in Paris (Arc de Triomphe) and La Rambla (as a young person), so yep, where there are tourists, there will be people trying to profit. 
Be safe 🌻",2026-05-02T13:48:44Z,2026-05-02T13:53:17Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:02:03.999245
