Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,UgwNqOPl3jUe9pjNyUN4AaABAg,,@happyhermit3141,"I'm amazed that the Champs Elysées in Paris isn't on the list. It fits all the criteria: overpriced, crowded, high level of pickpocketing and prostitution and hugely overrated. It's the type of place residents of Paris take their visiting friends who don't know any better. It isn't posh or refined by any stretch. OTOH, Père Lachaise cemetary, the second most visited landmark of Paris after the Eiffel Tower, is worth the detour. Just make sure you wear good walking boots with good ankle support if you go off the beaten path and explore some of the side passages that are barely wider than a large man's shoulders. Also, if you enter through the main entrance, your trek will be uphill all the way, including steep, uneven stone stairways. Instead, take the back entrance where the crematorium is located and your walk (except for the bit immediately after the entrance) will be all level or downhill. There are 110 acres to discover.",2026-05-02T10:25:23Z,2026-05-02T10:25:23Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:02:03.999277
Tourism,wFZyNQAIcdE,Ugw-O6opEE8kQEnGGbx4AaABAg,,@chopperskier,"We stopped in Cancun/Tolume/ Cozumel on a cruise.  Tolume (sp?) was great to see, but everything else there (other than the blue water) reminded me of the Bronx.  As a pilot, my company will not let me stay in certain 'dangerous' areas- they will have us reposition the plane somewhere else, or get us a limo to another part of town.  Hollywood is one of those places, along with DET (Detroit Metro), and of course anywhere inside NYC (Teterboro is considered far safer- HUGE EYE ROLL).  Lesson from a pilot- stay the F out of California, unless its Palm Springs, Santa Barbara, or Santa Ana.  Any way you slice it, you'll get lipstick on a pig in California.  Pure quality (over taxed and cancer Prop 65 laden...) GAHBAGE!

8 Euros at Temple Bar for a Guinness?  Ok, it's almost as expensive as every shit bar in America then!  Mt Rushmore: ""A long drive through remote terrain...""  One of the most beautiful drives in the country!  I was NOT disappointed by Mt Rushmore; not as great as you'd think but not disappointing.  To further your black hills trip, go climb the high point of South Dakota, maybe 20 minutes from Mt Rushmore.  A meandering 4 mile out and 4 mile back loop trail that is easy to walk, maintained, a very low grade (only 1,000' over the 4 miles), and a beautiful lookout tower up top!  If you can't find something in the Black Hills, you're probably a boring person.",2026-05-02T09:50:16Z,2026-05-02T10:15:30Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:02:03.999281
