AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUx_cfZgEHI,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@DMM6,@anthonysmurthwaite6258 How is a team that leaves the pitch for 17 minutes during a final robbed? Please explain that to me. Also Lyes is Algerian and his country literally celebrated for two full days after that final. Fireworks and all. So this video is very on-brand for them.,2026-03-29T22:43:26Z,2026-03-29T22:44:05Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:02:34.237739
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxc4KYvNjX,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@anthonysmurthwaite6258,"​@DMM6because the match ended, and Senegal won, if they ended the match when they left then fair enough (even if it's not at all impressive to win on a technicality) but to do that months after Senegal beat Morocco is a robbery, and considering Morocco were cheating all game, trying to take a towel and attacking the Senegalese player who was holding it, as well as getting a bunch of questionable referee decisions, it's ridiculous for Morocco to cry about it being unfair

Nobody outside of Moroccans takes this decision seriously, we all saw that Senegal beat Morocco in the final, overcoming blatant cheating and Senegal are the real champions",2026-03-29T23:04:49Z,2026-03-29T23:04:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:02:34.237743
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxezcXsLq3,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@DMM6,"@anthonysmurthwaite6258 You clearly are biased against morocco because you're talking absolute nonsense. How was Morocco cheating all game? Also, there is something called an APPEALS PROCESS, which is a legal recourse that every nation member of CAF are entitled to use in situations like this. You shouldn't be upset that Morocco exercised their legal right. You should be upset that Senegal left the pitch in the first place. According to the letter of the law, that's an automatic forfeit. 

As for your silly claim that nobody outside of Morocco takes the decision seriously, listen to Jose Mourinho talk about. Or even Nigeria's head coach (who was beat my Morocco). In the end, Morocco are the champions. Get over it.",2026-03-29T23:30:15Z,2026-03-29T23:31:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:02:34.237746
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxgPaRfXY7,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@anthonysmurthwaite6258,"​@DMM6not only was I not biased against Morocco, I actually liked Morocco more than Senegal before this ridiculous match, as for the appeals process, it's very weird that the people making this decision are the same people that let Morocco get away with harassing a Senegalese goalkeeper, almost as if there's some bias that would make them lean to certain decision, but since you're I should have no issue with this since it's their legal right, does that mean you'll be okay if it gets overturned again and Senegal wins, or will you cry about it?


Nobody might be a slight exaggeration, but 99.99999999% of people that aren't Moroccan and have no other reason or tendancy to support Morocco outside of the match agree that Morocco didn't win, because I don't know about you, but I tend to think if a team wins a trophy, they actually have to beat the team they're facing, which is what Senegal did, walk off or not, but winning a trophy after getting beat by the team that won the trophy without playing again does nothing, it's not impressive, there's nothing prestigious about winning a trophy in a courtroom, the lawyers are the only people who did anything for Morocco, non of the players or the manager did anything",2026-03-29T23:42:40Z,2026-03-29T23:42:40Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:02:34.237749
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxlRFR-yQf,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@DMM6,"@anthonysmurthwaite6258 Here's the thing, your opinion, and those who think like you, is 1000% irrelevant and inconsequential. It changes nothing. You are thinking emotionally and not practically.

The bottom line is this. Senegal abandoned the game. They forfeited the game. Morocco are champions. You cry about it all you want, it changes nothing.

And for what its worth, there are no winners in this situation. Senegal are rightly stripped of the title, and Morocco are robbed of the chance to celebrate with their fans in their own country. Everybody got shafted.",2026-03-30T00:26:35Z,2026-03-30T00:26:35Z,0,True,,2026-05-03T02:02:34.237752
