Tourisme,5dJJ2gfMPiY,UgwvOS6w2rbI4goqyip4AaABAg,,@margis.5873,"This is horrifying! I lived in Mexico for a couple of years when I was much younger, and I had the honor and Privilege of being invited by Oaxacan friends to join their family for the day of the dead In 1978. It was a small, quiet, and private ceremony. Very moving, and very honest. The elders spent the whole night in the cemetery, while we younger folk went back to their compound for the night. They were among the finest most generous people I've ever had the pleasure of knowing. I hate to think that their grandchildren's experience is being destroyed by egocentric tourist.😢",2026-03-18T14:46:12Z,2026-03-18T14:47:26Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-03T02:03:09.233863
