You really should study more instead of spouting off nonsense on subjects you know little about. All you're doing is advertising your ignorance. 

Jesus grew up in Nazareth, which was near what archaeology shows to have been the predominantly Greek-speaking city of Sepphoris. The distance between central Nazareth and the Roman theater at Sepphoris is barely 4mi (6.5km).

The Beatitudes (Matthew 5:3-12) contain numerous alliterations in the Greek text that simply wouldn’t exist in discourse delivered in Aramaic or Hebrew, suggesting these were originally spoken by Jesus in Greek. The location of the Sermon on the Mount, in the Decapolis region with its large Greek-speaking population and close to a known Greek-speaking city (Capernaum) in Galilee makes its delivery in Greek all the more likely.

